    • Method Detail

      • characters

        public static Iterable<Character> characters(CharSequence in)
        Returns an unmodifiable Iterable view of the Character values in in.

        Note: The returned Iterable maintains a defensive copy of the CharSequence, and any subsequent changes to the CharSequence will not be reflected when iterating.

        Parameters:
        in - a non-null CharSequence
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if in is null;

      • codePoints

        public static Iterable<Integer> codePoints(CharSequence in)

        Note: The returned Iterable maintains a defensive copy of the CharSequence, and any subsequent changes to the CharSequence will not be reflected when iterating.

        Parameters:
        in - a non-null CharSequence
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if in is null;

      • codePointsAsStrings

        public static Iterable<String> codePointsAsStrings(CharSequence in)
        Returns an unmodifiable Iterable view of the code points in in as instances of String.

        Note: The returned Iterable maintains a defensive copy of the CharSequence, and any subsequent changes to the CharSequence will not be reflected when iterating.

      • toCodePoint

        public static int toCodePoint(CharSequence in)
        Returns the int code point representation of a single Unicode character encoded in a CharSequence.
        Parameters:
        in - a non-null CharSequence containing a single Unicode character.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if in is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if in does not include exactly one Unicode character.
